Ben Agande Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Armed bandits on Wednesday night attacked the Good Shepherd Catholic Major Seminary, situated in Kakau, along Kaduna-Abuja road and made away with four seminarians. According to the Registrar of the school Rev Fr (Dr) Joel Usman, the incident happened between 10:30PM and 11:00 PM on Wednesday night. He said the “Good Shepherd Major Seminary was attacked by armed bandits yesterday January 8, 2020 between 10.30-11:00pm. ” After head count of students with security agents, 4 Seminarians have been declared missing. Kindly say a prayer for their release” Reverend Usman said in response to enquiries Police is yet to make a statement on the incidence as at the time of filing this report. 